<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-04-30T23:59:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-04-30T23:59:00-05:00" n="679" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d679">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/18031</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">War Department</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-30T23:59:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 30, 1916, 11.59 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Secretary of War directs you be informed as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>We, of course, cannot foresee result of further conference with
                                    General Obregon but suggest that if deadlock seems imminent you
                                    adjourn for further instructions from Department so as to gain
                                    time to pull together outlying parts of General Pershing’s
                                    force. Every precaution should be taken against sudden or
                                    general attack.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">McCain</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>